RIYADH: Saudi Foreign Minister Prince Faisal bin Farhan on Sunday met the Kuwaiti minister of foreign affairs and minister of state for cabinet affairs, Dr. Ahmed Nasser Mohammed Al-Sabah. During Prince Faisal’s visit to Kuwait, the two sides touched on ways to enhance bilateral coordination and joint action in various fields. They also discussed the most prominent developments in the regional and international arenas. They also reviewed aspects of the close fraternal relations that unite the Kingdom and Kuwait, and the deep bonds that link the leaderships and the peoples of the two countries. The meeting was attended by Prince Sultan bin Saad bin Khalid, the Saudi ambassador to Kuwait, and Abdulrahman Al-Daoud, the director general of the foreign minister’s office.